_Further reading_

* Turner, Fred. 2006. From Counterculture to Cyberculture: Stewart Brand, the Whole Earth Network and the Rise of Digital Utopianism. Chicago University Press.
* Singh, Simon. 1999. The Code Book: The Science of Secrecy from Ancient Egypt to Quantum Cryptography. Doubleday.
* Kahn, David. 1996. The Codebreakers: The Comprehensive History of Secret Communication from Ancient Times to the Internet. Scribner.
* Leavitt, David. 2006. The Man Who Knew Too Much: Alan Turing and the Invention of the Computer. W.W. Norton.
* Dyson, George. 2012. Turing's Cathedral: The Origins of the Digital Universe. Pantheon.
* Levy, Steven. 2010. Hackers: heroes of the computer revolution. O'Reilly publishing, 25th anniversary edition.

